<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> close the barn door after the horse gets out • your barn door is open</xh5><p> <i>close the barn door after the horse gets out—</i>not take any action until after a problem has already occurred: The problem is that post-accident testing <u>closes the barn door after the horse is long gone</u>.</p><p> <i>your barn door is open</i>—(U.S. euph.) is used as a caution to a man having his trouser zip undone: “Excuse me ... I couldn’t help but notice <u>your barn door is open</u>.” “What?” “Um ... your fly is open.”</p> </entry>
